Ejemplo 6.2

Agregar la expresi√≥n an√°litica de la serie en ambos formatos. Utilizar A =1.
Compact Trigonometric Fourier Series of a Periodic TriangleWave. Find the compact trigonometric Fourier series for the triangular periodic signal x(t) shown in Fig. 6.4a, and sketch the amplitude and phase spectra for x(t).

1.-Serie exponencial

t0=-0.5;
tf=1.5;
dn=@(n) -4*1i*sin(n*pi/2)/(n*pi)^2;
d0=0;
f=@(t) 2.*t.*(t>-0.5 & t<=0.5)+2.*(1-t).*(t>0.5 & t<1.5);
armo=15;
a=-4.5;
b=5.5;
w0=2*pi/(tf-t0);
sf=d0;
t=a:0.0001:b;
for n=1:armo
sf=sf+dn(-n)*exp(w0*-n*t*1i)+dn(n)*exp(w0*n*t*1i);
end
figure (1)
hFig = figure(1);
set(hFig, 'Position', [0 0 900 900])
subplot(3,2,1)
plot(t,sf,'LineWidth',2)
grid on
title('Serie exponencial compleja ','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
legend('Serie de Fourier','Location','Best')
xlabel('t','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
sf=d0;
t1=t0:0.0001:tf;
for n=1:armo
sf=sf+dn(-n)*exp(w0*-n*t1*1i)+dn(n)*exp(w0*n*t1*1i);
end
subplot(3,2,2)
hold off
plot(t1,f(t1),'r','LineWidth',2)
grid on
hold on
plot(t1,sf,'LineWidth',2)
legend('Funci√≥n original','Serie de Fourier ','Location','Best')
xlabel('t','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
nn=-armo:armo;
axis auto
subplot(3,2,4)
e=f(t1)-sf;
plot(t1,e,'LineWidth',2)
title('Error','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
xlabel('t','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
axis auto
grid on
subplot(3,2,6)
e=f(t1)-sf;
area(t1,e.^2)
legend('Energia del error','Location','Best')
xlabel('t','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
axis auto
grid on
absdn=zeros(1,length(nn));
cont=1;
for i =-armo:armo
if i==0
absdn(cont)=d0;
end
absdn(cont)=dn(i);
cont=cont+1;
end
subplot(3,2,3)
stem(w0*nn,abs(absdn),'LineWidth',2)
title('Espectro de magnitud D_n ','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
xlabel('\omega','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
grid on
subplot(3,2,5) % %
stem(w0*nn,angle(absdn),'LineWidth',2) % %
title('Espectro de fase, \angle de D_n ','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16) % %
xlabel('\omega','FontWeight','bold','FontSize',16)
grid on

2.- Serie trigonom√©trica

clearvars
cla reset;
d0=0;
dn=@(n) 2*cos(pi*n)/(pi*n);

tf=1;
f=@(t) t;

b=5;
w0=2*pi/(tf-t0);
sf=d0;

for n=1:armo
sf=sf+dn(n)*cos(n.*w0.*t+pi/2);
end
